trans-unit.source: Provides methods and properties used to navigate the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] tree.
trans-unit.target: Fornece métodos e as propriedades utilizadas para navegar o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] árvore.

trans-unit.source: UI Automation clients view the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elements on the desktop as a set of <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> objects arranged in a tree structure.
trans-unit.target: Os clientes de automatização de IU ver o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elementos no ambiente de trabalho como um conjunto de <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>dispostos numa estrutura de árvore de objetos.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>

trans-unit.source: Using the TreeWalker class, a client application can navigate the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] tree by selecting a view of the tree and stepping from one <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> to another in a specified direction using the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetFirstChild%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetLastChild%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetPreviousSibling%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetNextSibling%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetParent%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: Utilizar a classe de TreeWalker, uma aplicação cliente pode navegar o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] árvore selecionando uma vista de árvore e avance a partir de um <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>para outro numa direção especificada através do <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetFirstChild%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetLastChild%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetPreviousSibling%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetNextSibling%2A>, e <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetParent%2A>métodos.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetParent%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetNextSibling%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetPreviousSibling%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetLastChild%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.GetFirstChild%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>

trans-unit.source: Navigating the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] tree using TreeWalker can result in cross-process calls and is not as efficient as locating an element using the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.FindAll%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.FindFirst%2A> methods.
trans-unit.target: Navegar o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] árvore com TreeWalker pode resultar em processos cruzados de chamadas e não é tão eficiente como localizar um elemento utilizando o <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.FindAll%2A>ou <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.FindFirst%2A>métodos.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.FindFirst%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.FindAll%2A>

trans-unit.source: If your client application might try to find elements in its own user interface, you must make all [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] calls on a separate thread.
trans-unit.target: Se a aplicação cliente poderá tentar encontrar elementos na sua própria interface de utilizador, tem de se todos os [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] chama num thread separado.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> can have additional sibling elements that do not match the current view condition and thus are not returned when navigating the element tree.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>pode ter elementos de colaterais adicionais que não correspondem a condição de vista atual e, consequentemente, não são devolvidos quando navegar a árvore de elemento.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>

trans-unit.source: The structure of the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> tree changes as the visible [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_ui](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-ui-md.md)] elements on the desktop change.
trans-unit.target: A estrutura do <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>árvore alterações, como o visível [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_ui](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-ui-md.md)] elementos a alteração de ambiente de trabalho.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement>

trans-unit.source: It is not guaranteed that an element returned as the previous sibling element will be returned as the previous sibling on subsequent passes.
trans-unit.target: Não é garantido que um elemento devolvido como elemento colateral anterior será devolvido como o colateral anterior pela transmite subsequentes.

trans-unit.source: The element from which to retrieve the previous sibling.
trans-unit.target: O elemento a partir do qual pretende obter o colateral anterior.

trans-unit.source: The previous sibling element, or a null reference (<xref uid="langword_csharp_Nothing" name="Nothing" href=""></xref> in [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_visualbnet](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-visualbnet-md.md)]) if there is no such element.

trans-unit.source: Retrieves the node itself, if it satisfies the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.Condition*>, or the nearest parent or ancestor node that satisfies the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker.Condition*>.
trans-unit.target: Obtém o próprio, o nó se satisfazem a <> </> *>, ou o nó principal ou o predecessor mais próximo que satisfaça os <> </> *>.

trans-unit.source: The element is normalized by navigating up the ancestor chain in the tree until an element that satisfies the view condition for the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker> object is reached.
trans-unit.target: O elemento é normalizado navegando se a cadeia de predecessor na árvore da até um elemento que satisfaça a condição de vista para o <xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker>objeto for atingido.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker>

trans-unit.source: If the root element is reached, the root element is returned even if it does not satisfy the view condition.
trans-unit.target: Se o elemento raiz for atingido, o elemento raiz é devolvido, mesmo que não satisfaz a condição de vista.

trans-unit.source: This method is useful for applications that obtain references to [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elements by hit-testing.
trans-unit.target: Este método é útil para aplicações que obtêm as referências a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elementos por acessos de teste.

trans-unit.source: The application might want to work only with specific types of elements, and can use Normalize to make sure that no matter what element is initially retrieved (for example, when a scroll bar gets the input focus), only the element of interest (such as a content element) is ultimately retrieved.
trans-unit.target: A aplicação poderá querer só funcionam com tipos de elementos específicos e pode utilizar a normalização para se certificar de que, independentemente do que elemento inicialmente é obtido (por exemplo, quando uma barra de deslocamento obtém o foco de entrada), apenas o elemento de interesses (por exemplo, um elemento de conteúdo), em última análise é obtido.

trans-unit.source: The element from which to start the normalization.
trans-unit.target: O elemento a partir do qual pretende iniciar a normalização.

trans-unit.source: The nearest <xref href="System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement"></xref> in the current view.
trans-unit.target: O mais próximo <xref href="System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement"> </xref> na vista atual.

trans-unit.source: If the navigation up the ancestor chain reaches the root element, the root element is returned.
trans-unit.target: Se configurar a cadeia de predecessor painel de navegação atinge o elemento de raiz, é devolvido o elemento raiz.

trans-unit.source: If your client application might try to find elements in its own user interface, you must make all [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] calls on a separate thread.
